
<p>Darjeeling, the most beautiful destination in west bengal, is a charming hill station that is popular for its authentic natural beauty. Explore the cloudy green mountains, colonial heritage and famous tea gardens in Darjeeling with our Darjeeling tour packages.</p>

<p>Our Darjeeling tour packages offer a true escape to a world of scenic beauty that never fails to stun its visitors. You can explore all the top tourist places and adventure activities in Darjeeling with easy transportation and comfortable stay with invisit. Book Darjeeling travel packages now.</p>

<h2>Best Time to Visit Darjeeling</h2>
<p>April to June are considered the best times to visit Darjeeling. However, it depends on your preference, but during this period, you can have the best experience of Darjeeling.</p>

<h3>How to Reach Darjeeling</h3>

<p><strong>By Air</strong>- You need to take a flight to Bagdora Airport (IXB), later, you can depart for Darjeeling via local bus or Volvo.</p>

<p><strong>By Train</strong>- Take the train to New Jalpaiguri station, which is approximately 88 km away, then you can take public transport to reach Darjeeling.</p>

<p><strong>By Road</strong>- Darjeeling is well connected to nearby cities, you can easily get into Darjeeling via road.</p>

<h2>Best Places to visit in Darjeeling / Top Tourist Places to Visit in Darjeeling</h2>

<h3>Rolling Tea Garden</h3>
<p>Alluring tea fields in Darjeeling, that look like a soft green carpet, are one of the best places to visit in Darjeeling. These Darjeeling tea are popular for its delicate aroma and distinct muscatel flavor.</p>

<h3>Himalayan Railway</h3>
<p>Take a ride on the UNSECO World heritage Darjeeling Himalayan Railway, a narrow steam engine popularly known as Toy Train. Take a ride on this famous toy train that lets you witness the beautiful view of Darjeeling.</p>

<h3>Tiger Hill</h3>
<p>Witness a spectacular sunrise over Kanchenjunga from Tiger Hill, one of the most popular view points in Darjeeling. Book darjeeling tour packages with invisit.</p>

<h3>Batasia Loop</h3>
<p>While on Darjeeling trip, don&rsquo;t miss out on enjoying a unique train ride on the Batasia Loop, which is one of the best places to visit in Darjeeling. Book darjeeling travel packages and enjoy Batasia Loop with your family and friends.</p>

<h3>Ghoom Monastrery</h3>
<p>Ghoom Monastery, a traditional Buddhist monastery with a long statue of Maitreya Buddha, is one of the best places to visit in Darjeeling. Book darjeeling tour packages with invisit to get an exciting deal on Darjeeling Packages.</p>

<h3>Happy Valley</h3>
<p>Visit one of the oldest tea gardens in Darjeeling, Happy Valley is the top tourist place to visit in Darjeeling. Take a tour of the Happy Valley and learn more about tea production.</p>

<h2>Top Things to do in Darjeeling / Best Activities in Darjeeling</h2>

<h3>Stay at a Tea Garden</h3>
<p>Tea excursions are not a new concept in Darjeeling. The hill station is endowed with many spreading tea gardens. Darjeeling, known as the 'Mecca of tea', contains over 80 operating tea estates. The tea gardens are a famous tourist attraction in Darjeeling.</p>

<h3>Drive up to Tiger Hill </h3>
<p>Tiger Hill in Darjeeling is a renowned tourist destination. The lovely overlook at an elevation of 8482 feet provides amazing views of the sun rising over the spectacular snow-covered mountains of the Himalayas.</p>

<h3>Visit the Himalayan Mountaineering Institute</h3>
<p>The Himalayan Mountaineering Institute is a must-visit for any climber. Mt. Kanchenjunga is a must-see destination for adventurers from all over the world.</p>

<h3>Explore colonial connections</h3>
<p>British residents in India have fallen in love with the beautiful beauty of Darjeeling. While exploring Darjeeling's colonial history, experience the magnificent 19th-century lifestyle at the Windamere Hotel or the Glenburn Tea Estate.</p>

<h3>All aboard the Joy Ride &lsquo;Toy Train&rsquo;</h3>

<p>Darjeeling is well-known across the world for its stunning scenery and magnificent mountain railway. The narrow gauge line that operates the 'Toy Train' is a marvel of engineering and construction and a UNESCO World Heritage property.</p>

<h3>Darjeeling Ropeway</h3>

<p>The breathtaking vistas of Darjeeling have captivated you, but for an even more enjoyable experience, take a ride on the Darjeeling Ropeway. The Rangeet Valley Passenger Cable Car is one of the best ways to see the magnificent vistas that the hill station in North East India is famed for.</p>

